FBIS4-2426 "drchi069_v_94007" FBIS-CHI-94-069 Daily Report 11 Apr 1994 TAIWAN Premier: PRC Handling of Qiandao Tragedy `Inhuman' Premier: PRC Handling of Qiandao Tragedy `Inhuman' Ministry May Stop Mainland Investments OW1104095194 Taipei Voice of Free China in English 0200 GMT 11 Apr 94 OW1104095194 Taipei Voice of Free China English BFN [From the "News" program] [Text] The Ministry of Economic Affairs has announced plans to bar ROC [Republic of China] investors, for the time being, from sinking further amounts of capital into the development of industrial parks in the mainland. The general disgust with conditions on the mainland enlisted by the boat tragedy may furnish the harsh warning ROC economic planners have been looking for to cool mainland investment fever.
